  "title": "Negative ions of carbon, nitrogen, and phosphorus",
  "abstract": "Negative ions of the nitrogen atom have yet to be observed. We estimate the electron affinity of the ${\\mathrm{N}}^{\\ensuremath{-}}$ system to be approximately $\\ensuremath{-}0.181$ eV using the multiconfiguration Dirac-Fock method. Similar calculations for the neighboring (same row) ${\\mathrm{C}}^{\\ensuremath{-}}$ and (same column) ${\\mathrm{P}}^{\\ensuremath{-}}$ system yield, respectively, 1.210 eV and 0.702 eV, in good agreement with measurements: respectively, 1.263 eV and 0.746 eV. The discrepancies that remain are primarily due to core-core and core-valence correlation effects that have been neglected. The improbability of the existence of a stable ${\\mathrm{N}}^{\\ensuremath{-}}$ system is already evident from a comparison of much simpler calculations with measurements for systems in the same row and neighboring row of the Periodic Table.",
